<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Cuba-Guevara     06-15 0137</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Cuba-Guevara,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Concert Marks 60th Birthday of Late Revolutionary Hero</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 200,000 people attended a concert
in Havana to mark what would have been the 60th birthday of the
late revolutionary hero Ernesto ``Che'' Guevara, the Prensa Latina
news agency said.
   The dispatch from the official Cuban agency, received in Mexico
City, said the Monday night concert spilled over into the early
morning hours in the city's huge Plaza of the Revolution.
   Elsewhere in Cuba, ``in the name of Che, workers massively
donated labor, artists gave concerts, newspapers, radio and
television filled their spaces, children recited poems and doves
flew at midnight,'' Prensa Latina said.
   Guevara, born in Argentina in 1928, became a hero of the
revolution that brought Fidel Castro to power in 1959. He later was
killed in Bolivia.
</TEXT>
