<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Hat Sentence,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Given 10 Years For Stealing 36 Hats</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A thief who was tracked down by police
following his four-block trail of stolen hats was sentenced to 10
years in prison.
   The sentence imposed Monday on 27-year-old Lavon King was double
the state-prescribed guideline.
   Circuit Judge David C. Wiggins said King was a habitual offender
with a long criminal record.
   King was convicted May 24 of the March break-in of Heyman's
Department Store.
   When King and another man were spotted outside the store by
police, they began running and tossing away the hats they had
stuffed under their shirts. A trail of 36 hats led police to King.
The other man was never arrested.
