<NOTE>Eds: Members who used a0532, PM-AIDS Conference, 1st Ld -Writethru
to a0425, sent June 13 under a Stockholm, Sweden, dateline, are
asked to use the following.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press quoted Dr.
Jonathan Mann erroneously on June 13 as saying that in Bangkok,
Thailand, 1 percent of the population had antibodies to AIDS in
1987 and that in the first three months of 1988, the infection had
spread to 16 percent of Bangkok's population.
   In both instances, Mann was referring to the percentage of drug
abusers seeking treatment in Bangkok who were found to be carrying
antibodies to acquired immune deficiency syndrome, and not to the
population as a whole.
