<HEAD>Storm Kills Five, Leaves 5,000 Homeless</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A powerful storm pounded western
Bangladesh, killing five people, flattening mud huts and leaving
about 5,000 people homeless, police said today.
   About 2,000 homes were destroyed in the storm Monday night in
Kushtia district, about 60 miles west of the capital, police said
by telephone on condition of anonymity.
   About 200 people were injured, most when their houses collapsed.
At least 50 were hospitalized.
   The storm, packing winds of up to 80 mph, lashed the area for
about 30 minutes, uprooting hundreds of trees, toppling utility
polls and damaging rice crops, police said.
