<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Molestation-Teacher     06-15 0275</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Molestation-Teacher,0286</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teacher-Scout Leader Sentenced to Life for Fondling 16 Boys</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 42-year-old former teacher of the year was
sentenced to life in prison for fondling as many as 16 boys.
   District Judge John Ovard issued the sentence Tuesday at a
jury's recommendation.
   The jury took 90 minutes to decide that John Earl McGrew, a Boy
Scout leader, should serve a life term on one count of aggravated
sexual assault of a child and 20 years each on two counts of
indecency with a child.
   He also was fined $5,000 on each count. The prison sentences,
the maximum in each case, will run concurrently.
   McGrew, who was convicted Monday following a three-week trial,
said he will appeal.
   ``I am innocent of this crime and I will be moving to the next
step to prove my innocence,'' McGrew said at a news conference
after the sentencing.
   Defense attorney John Weddle had asked jurors to place McGrew on
probation, citing his numerous awards for work with the Boy Scouts
and his selection as his elementary school's 1986 teacher of the
year.
   McGrew claims he was the victim of a conspiracy, but would not
elaborate.
   Prosecutor Faith Johnson said Johnson was ``a typical fixated
pedophile and he doesn't want to admit he's guilty.''
   McGrew, who taught at John J. Rhoads Elementary School in south
Dallas, was arrested in December after an 11-year-old former pupil
said the teacher fondled him in the classroom in the fall of 1984.
   In addition to the three complaining witnesses, 13 other
children testified that McGrew fondled them. Eight children
testifying on behalf of McGrew said he never touched them.
</TEXT>
