<2ND_LINE>PM-Motorist Slaying,0224</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>18-Year-Old Charged in Death of Motorist Hit by Concrete Block</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT MYERS, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man has been arrested on charges he
dropped a 50-pound concrete block through a car windshield from an
overpass, killing the driver.
   Mark Weston Casey, 18, of North Fort Myers, was charged Tuesday
with manslaughter, throwing a deadly missile into a vehicle and
leaving the scene of a fatal accident, said the Highway Patrol.
   The concrete block caused Rodrick McDuff's station wagon to
careen out of control and flip over Jan. 19 on an interstate
highway. McDuff, 32, of Fort Myers, was returning home from a
business trip just before midnight.
   Casey was taken Tuesday to the Southwest Florida Juvenile
Detention Center, said Lt. Malcolm Rhodes. Prosecutors have not
determined whether he will be tried as an adult or juvenile. Casey
was 17 at the time of the accident.
   If convicted, he faces up to 25 years in prison.
   Rhodes said that with no witnesses, ``We're very lucky to get an
arrest.'' He said only that troopers talked to people who had
knowledge of the accident.
   McDuff was a district supervisor for the Rite Aid Corp. The
pharmacy chain offered a $5,000 reward and volunteered two of its
private investigators to help on the case.
</TEXT>
