<HEAD>Small Bills Bring Big Charges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Elitrous Faye Squires brought $7,200 in
small bills to bail a friend out of jail and landed behind bars
herself.
   The man Ms. Squires was trying to free, Creadell Hubbard, 31,
had been charged with robbing a credit union at gunpoint.
   ``It wasn't _ lucky for us _ a very smart move,'' said police
Sgt. W.L. Baker. ``If somebody is arrested for bank robbery and
somebody comes in with small bills (for bail), it's obvious.''
   Ms. Squires, 25, was arrested Monday on a charge of possession
of stolen property _ money taken in the holdup. Most of the money
was in $10 and $20 bills, Baker said.
   Hubbard remained behind behind bars. Ms. Squires was freed on
$1,000 bail Monday.
