<HEAD>Ranking Self-Defense Force Official Commits Suicide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A senior official of Japan's Maritime Self-Defense
Force committed suicide today by jumping from the sixth floor of an
apartment building, a Defense Agency spokesman said.
   Yoshifumi Wada, 48, chief of the Aircraft Division at the
Maritime Staff Office, was found dead by a resident of the building
east of Tokyo, said spokesman Lt. Cmdr. Yutaka Nojima.
   He said the Maritime Self-Defense Force and local police were
investigating the suicide.
   Nojima said Wada had been undergoing questioning since Saturday
by officials concerning allegations he was ``frequently
entertained'' by Japanese companies seeking work contracts. The
Aircraft Division handles procurement for the force and repairs its
aircraft.
