<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--France-Drugs     06-15 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--France-Drugs,0130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pineapple Cans Yield Year's Biggest Cocaine Seizure In France</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police found 385 pounds of cocaine hidden in cases
of canned pineapple and arrested four Colombians, officials said
Wednesday.
   Bernart Gravet, head of the French anti-drug squad, said the $10
million worth of cocaine was found Monday during a raid on a
northern Paris warehouse.
   It was the largest seizure of cocaine this year in France.
   Gravet said the raid occurred while a shipment of 17,500 cans of
pineapple was being unloaded at the warehouse. Police found that
460 of the cans contained plastic envelopes of cocaine instead of
canned pineapple.
   He said the cocaine was intended for distribution in West
Germany, Britain and the Netherlands as well as in France.
</TEXT>
