<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--MilitaryMoves     06-15 0151</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Military Moves,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fornell to Replace Chubb in Air Force Electronic Systems Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan has nominated Maj. Gen.
Gordon E. Fornell, the Air Force general who serves as the top
military aide to Defense Secretary Frank C. Carlucci, for a
promotion and new assignment, the Pentagon said Wednesday.
   Assuming he is confirmed by the Senate, Fornell will receive a
third star and the rank of lieutenant general and become the next
chief of the electronic systems division of the Air Force Systems
Command _ a position with important contracting responsibilities.
   Fornell, 51, is a native of Chicago.
   The Pentagon said Air Force Lt. Gen. Melvin F. Chubb Jr., who
holds the post now, planned to retire on Oct. 1 after more than 34
years of active-duty service.
   Chubb, 54, is a native of Joplin, Mo., who has held the
electronic systems division command since July 1984.
</TEXT>
