<FILEID>AP-NR-06-15-88 1254EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r p AM-BRF--VaCongress     06-15 0179</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Va Congress,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Arey Abandons District After Losing Election</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DANVILLE, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former White House aide who denied she
had moved back to Danville just to run for Congress said Wednesday
after losing the election that she is returning to Washington.
   ``I'm putting my house on the market today,'' Linda Arey told
The Bee hours after unofficial returns Tuesday night showed her
losing the southside 5th District congressional race to Democrat
L.F. Payne Jr., the developer of a ski and golf resort.
   Ms. Arey had said during the campaign that her heart never left
her home town although she lived out of the district for 12 years
while she went to law school and later held several posts in the
Reagan administration.
   Her husband, Barney Skladany, is a Washington corporate attorney
for Mobil Oil and a congressional lobbyist.
   The final count showed Payne with 55,406 votes or 59 percent to
Ms. Arey's 38,086 votes or 41 percent.
   The incumbent, conservative Democrat W.C. ``Dan'' Daniel, died
of a heart attack in January while serving his 10th term.
</TEXT>
