<HEAD>Flag Lover Pleads Innocent to Violating Noise Codes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man whose giant American flag flaps
too loudly for his neighbors pleaded innocent _ on Flag Day, no
less _ to violating noise codes.
   Thomas Demski held a Flag Day ceremony at his home for hundreds
of spectators before going off to Municipal Court on Tuesday.
   He has refused to take down his 47-by-82-foot flag atop a
132-foot pole. Demski said that he doesn't think his flag is that
noisy and that sometimes it is too windy to take the banner down
without risking tearing it.
   He faces up to six months in jail and a $500 fine if convicted
of the misdemeanor.
