<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BoyStabber     06-15 0184</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Boy Stabber,0189</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Boy Sentenced to 12 Years in Prison</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 13-year-old boy who pleaded
guilty to breaking into a neighbor's house and stabbing her was
sentenced as an adult to 12 years in prison.
   Jason Williams of Hallandale was sentenced Tuesday by Broward
Circuit Judge Leroy Moe after he pleaded guilty to charges of
attempted first-degree murder and armed burglary.
   The boy, 5 feet, 100 pounds, twice stabbed 64-year-old Delores
Barber on Jan. 31 after borrowing a cup of sugar from her a few
hours earlier, authorities said.
   He had no previous record and lacked a motive, lawyers and the
judge said.
   Because of the violence of the attack, he was treated as an
adult. But he will not be imprisoned with adults, said Louis
Carmichael, a correctional services administrator. He will be put
in with younger inmates, few of whom are as young as he is.
   ``If he doesn't really understand why he did this, maybe he will
be able to figure it out,'' said Douglas McNeill, the boy's lawyer.
   Ms. Barber recovered from her injuries.
</TEXT>
