<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Olympic figure skating champion Katarina Witt will
be host at a rock concert in East Berlin on Sunday, while American
superstar Michael Jackson is performing in West Berlin.
   Witt, 22, won her second Olympic gold medal in Calgary in
February and won her fouth world title in Budapest a month later.
Sunday's concert features the Dutch group, Bots Netherland, and
East Germany's group City.
   ``I like rock and all the music that young people like,'' Witt
said. ``Music unites people.''
   The concert is in competition with an outdoor performance by
Jackson that same evening. Last year, East German fans of Jackson
demonstrated in the streets when another open-air concert could be
heard across the wall separating the cities.
