<HEAD>Democrats Plans to Serve Bologna at Bush's Houston Address</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Some Texas Democrats are planning to serve
bologna to fellow party members in the hotel suite that Vice
President George Bush lists as his legal residence.
   Democratic National Committee member Billie Carr of Houston and
Austin party activist Ty Fain have rented the Houstonian Hotel
suite that Bush cites as his legal address.
   ``It's baloney for him to claim his residence is Texas,'' Carr
said.
   To illustrate their opinion, the two plan to serve bologna at
the suite to fellow Democrats Friday in conjunction with the Texas
Democratic Convention, which begins that evening in Houston.
   Bush, who has wrapped up the GOP presidential nomination, lived
in Texas for years but hasn't owned a local residence since
becoming vice president in 1981. He was born in Massachusetts, grew
up in Connecticut, has a vacation home in Maine and votes in
Houston.
