<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Robertson-CBN,170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Robertson Says CBN Down, Not Out</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIRGINIA BEACH, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pat Robertson is predicting a quick
return to financial health for his Christian Broadcasting Network,
which suffered when he left it to run for the Republican
presidential nomination.
   Still, Robertson said in an interview published Wednesday in the
Daily Press of Newport News, ``We're in serious trouble here. If
the decline had continued over a period of a year or so, the
survival of this organization would have been very much in doubt.''
   Robertson, who founded the network almost 30 years ago,
collected less than 50 delegates after spending nearly $27 million
on his campaign, which he suspended last month.
   ``I do not wish to get back into politics,'' Robertson said.
``Politics is not fun. CBN is fun.'' He did not, however, rule out
another run for the presidency.
   ``I'm not going to rule anything out because I just don't know
what is going to happen,'' he said.
