<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Germany-Escape     06-15 0175</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Germany-Escape,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Border Guard Shoots Sergeant, Swims River To Flee To West Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HANOVER, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An East German soldier shot another
guard in the foot Wednesday, plunged into the nearby Elbe River and
swam to safety in West Germany, police in Hanover said.
   West German border police said the escape took place as the
soldier and a sergeant were on guard duty about 30 miles southeast
of Hamburg, where the river forms the border between the two German
states.
   In remote areas along the communist line of fences and barriers
separating East Germany from West Germany, East German border
guards work in pairs to discourage escapes.
   After shooting the sergeant in the foot to prevent him from
interfering with the escape, the 23-year-old East German soldier
dived into the river and swam 500 feet to safety in a West German
border patrol boat, police said.
   Police said the East German soldier cited dissatisfaction with
conditions in his homeland as his reason for fleeing.
   No other details surrounding the escape were released.
</TEXT>
