<HEAD>Senate Leader Calls for Appointment of Special Envoy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Senate's Democratic and Republican leaders
urged the Reagan administration on Wednesday to appoint a special
envoy to pursue U.S. interests in Afghanistan as the withdrawal of
Soviet troops is completed.
   Majority Leader Robert C. Byrd, D-W.Va., and Minority Leader Bob
Dole, R-Kan., said naming an ambassador-at-large for Afghanistan
for a six-month period would ``send a needed signal to the
