Banking Committee Chairman William Proxmire, D-Wis., and others.
   But House Agriculture Committee Chairman Kika de la Garza,
D-Texas, on Tuesday praised its members for their ``political
courage'' last month in recommending preservation, for the most
part, of the regulatory status quo.
</TEXT>
