   A big block of Texaco Inc. stock has changed
hands, but it was unknown who participated in the sale or what it
might mean for the impending proxy showdown between the oil giant
and financier Carl C. Icahn.
   The New York Stock Exchange reported Tuesday that 7,696,300
shares, representing 3.2 percent of Texaco's 243 million shares
outstanding, sold at $50.25 per share.
   Some analysts said the buyer may have been Icahn, who has
offered to buy the Texaco shares he does not already own for $60 a
share. Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co., an investment firm known to
have held a 4.9 percent stake in Texaco, was seen as a likely
seller.
</TEXT>
