<HEAD>IBM Tops Magazine's List Of Biggest Computer Companies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   International Business Machines Corp. retained
its domination of the world computer industry in 1987 despite a
modest 6 percent increase in its information-systems revenue,
according to trade publication.
   Datamation magazine on Tuesday released its annual list of
companies ranked by how much money they take in from information
systems, which range from computers to facsimile machines,
computerized cash registers and automatic teller machines.
   Here are Datamation's top 10 companies, along with their
headquarters, their information-systems revenue, and their 1986
rank:
   1. International Business Machines Corp., Armonk, N.Y., $50.5
billion, no change.
   2. Digital Equipment Corp., Maynard, Mass., $10.4 billion, up
from third.
   3. Unisys Corp., Detroit, Mich., $8.742 billion, down from
second.
   4. Fujitsu Ltd., Tokyo, $8.740 billion, no change.
   5. NEC Corp., Tokyo, $8.23 billion, no change.
   6. Hitachi Ltd., Tokyo, $6.27 billion, no change.
   7. Siemens AG, Munich, West Germany, $5.70 billion, up from
eighth.
   8. NCR Corp., Dayton, Ohio, $5.08 billion, up from ninth.
   9. Hewlett-Packard Co., Palo Alto, Calif., $5.00 billion, down
from seventh.
   10. Ing. C. Olivetti & Co. SpA, Ivrea, Italy, $4.64 billion, no
change.
