<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street Noon,0358</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market held at slightly lower levels
today after traders moved to cash in on profits following a strong
rally in the previous session.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, which surged 25 points
to a post-crash high on Tuesday, was off 5.87 points at 2,118.60 by
midday.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 74.39 million shares. Losers
outnumbered gainers by about 11 to 8 with 533 up, 751 down and 503
unchanged as of noon on Wall Street.
   Traders said there was some uncertainty in the market today
following Tuesday's rally, which was sparked by a
better-than-expected trade report for April.
   Stocks were off slightly at the opening on basic profit-taking,
but prices dipped further when the commodity markets opened on the
high side.
   ``Corn and soybeans were up the limit,'' noted Charles Jensen,
chief technical analyst at MKI Securities Corp. Bond prices
softened in turn because of the implication of higher inflation,
and stock prices began to retreat, he said.
   ``We're overdue for a pretty nice correction,'' Jensen said.
``Any setback would be the normal thing to expect.''
   But the tone remains optimistic. Several technicians revised
their market forecasts favorably today.
   In addition, money managers, who have an unusually high amount
of cash on hand, are looking to buy equities for their portfolios
as the second quarter draws to a close. As one trader said, ``They
want to hop aboard the train before it leaves the station.''
   Dealers said the market had little interest in government
reports that showed retail sales rose 0.1 percent and industrial
production rose 0.4 percent, both seasonally adjusted, in May.
   Among actively traded issues, Texaco was down ] at 50, Exxon was
down { at 46\, Zenith was up 1} at 26[, Chrysler was off \ at 24~,
and Philip Morris was up \ at 83}.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks fell
0.63 to 153.89. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was off 0.42 at 308.46.
</TEXT>
