<HEAD>Modest Rise For London Shares</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: updates with close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices closed modestly higher on the London Stock
Exchange Wednesday after Tuesday's sharp rise.
   At the end of trading, the Fiancial Times-Stock Exchange
100-stock index was up 3.1 points, or 0.16 percent, at 1,869.3.
Trading volume was a healthy 551.7 million shares, compared with
Tuesday's 472.8 million.
   The Dow Jones industrial average was down 3.56 points at 2120.91
near the close of trading in London.
   Brokers said they were disappointed that the New York market
didn't continue to rise on Tuesday's good news of the narrowing of
the U.S. trade deficit to $9.89 billion in April. They said London
shares seem more responsive to the American trade figures.
