<HEAD>Inflation Up in May in France</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Inflation in France rose between 0.2 percent and
0.3 percent in May, compared to the previous month, according to
provisional figures released Wednesday by the National Statistics
Institute.
   Since the beginning of the year, prices have risen 1.4 percent.
In the past 12 months, they rose between 2.5 percent and 2.6
percent.
   In April, inflation was 0.5 percent and in March it was 0.3
percent, the institute said.
