<HEAD>Coleco CEO Undergoes Heart Surgery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Morton E. Handel, Coleco Industries
Inc.'s chairman and chief executive officer, has undergone coronary
bypass surgery and will be out of work for at least two weeks, the
company said.
   Handel, 53, was resting comfortably after surgery Tuesday at St.
Francis Hospital and Medical Center in Hartford, Coleco spokeswoman
Barbara Wruck said.
   Handel, who was named chairman and chief executive officer in
May, has been leading negotiations with Coleco's bankers and
creditors as the toymaker tries to avoid filing for protection from
creditors in U.S. Bankruptcy Court.
   Coleco has almost no cash, has curtailed production, slashed its
staff size and arranged for short-term financing through June 30.
It has also offered a number of its product lines for sale to raise
cash.
   The company, manufacturer of Cabbage Patch Kids dolls, has set a
June 30 deadline for arranging an exchange of debt securities.
   Wruck said Coleco President J. Brian Clarke will step in for
Handel until the chairman has recovered.
   She said Handel ``expects to rsume partial business functions''
in two weeks.
</TEXT>
