<TEXT>
   Allstate Insurance Co. said Wednesday it
plans to sell some of the group life and health insurance
operations of its Allstate Life Insurance Co. subsidiary.
   Allstate, a subsidiary of Sears, Roebuck and Co., said it would
sell its corporate accounts and group brokerage operations, which
account for less than 20 percent of Allstate Life Insurance's total
revenues, the company said. Group pension and agent group
operations will not be affected.
