<HEAD>Weekly Petroleum Review</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Total crude oil runs to stills averaged
13,665,000 barrels daily during the week ended Friday, June 6, the
American Petroleum Institute reported Wednesday. This compared with
13,812,000 barrels daily in the previous week and 12,919,000
barrels daily a year earlier.
   Crude runs east of California averaged 11,038,000 barrels daily
compared with 11,100,000 the previous week and 10,534,000 a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to
6,700,000 barrels a day, compared with 6,889,000 barrels a day in
the previous week and 7,122,000 a day a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline production was 5,626,000 a day
compared with 5,834,000 a day last week and 5,977,000 a day a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were
222,075,000 barrels, versus 224,048,000 a week earlier and
232,624,000 a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline stocks totaled 193,777,000
barrels, compared with 194,814,000 in the previous week and
200,488,000 barrels last year.
   Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production
for the week ended Friday was 8,236,000 barrels compared with
8,279,000 last year.
   Crude oil stocks totaled 360,236,000 barrels at the close of
last week, against 361,568,000 a week previous and 322,172,000 a
year ago.
   East of California crude stocks amounted to 285,099,000 barrels,
compared with 282,856,000 a week earlier.
   Daily imports east of California for the week ended Friday were
crude oil, 5,482,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 401,000,
distillate fuel oil, 57,O00, and others 1,088,500, a total of
7,028,000 barrels.
   California imports were: crude oil 43,000 barrels, and products
31,000, a total of 74,000 barrels, for a grand total of 7,102,000.
   For the four weeks, daily imports east of California were crude
oil 5,116,000 barrels, residual fuel oil 199,000, distillate fuel
oil 77,000, and others 604,000, for a total of 5,996,000 barrels.
   For the four weeks, California daily imports averaged for crude
oil 216,000 barrels, products 66,000, a total of 282,000 barrels,
for a grand total of 6,278,000 barrels.
   The following table shows comparative daily production of the
other principal refined products for the U.S. as a whole and east
of California. Also shown are the comparative stock totals for
certain refined products.
